title: How to troubleshoot: Cannot Connect to Internet
content:
Background:
The issue of 'Cannot Connect to Internet' is commonly encountered in Dell laptops due to various hardware or software malfunctions.

Symptoms:
Users may experience symptoms such as system freezes, inability to boot, connectivity drops, or system errors related to 'Cannot Connect to Internet'.

Resolution:
To resolve the 'Cannot Connect to Internet', follow these steps: 1) Perform a power cycle. 2) Update the BIOS and drivers. 3) Check for hardware malfunctions. 4) Contact Dell support if the issue persists.
